file:        c5_slave_merged.bin
chip:        esp32c5
flash-size:  4 MB
flash-mode:  dio
flash-freq:  80 MHz
flash-at:    0x0
size-bytes:  1561584
size-human:  1.5 MB
sha256:      55ce02867548ceae84e2b96fcc663266620c0608cad3d3fb5f13349fbb6c77c0

upstream:    https://github.com/espressif/esp-hosted-mcu @ f99ee55aea93ab671d9849bd962aa2f10d01f7d5
idf:         v6.0
target:      esp32c5

phy-hack:
  - phy_11p_set(1, 0) armed at boot and on every WIFI_EVENT_WIFI_READY
  - country set to "01" with WIFI_COUNTRY_POLICY_MANUAL (allows ITS channels)
  - bootstrap channel = 140, then phy_change_channel(180, 1, 0, 0)
  - WIFI_PS_NONE
  - phy_agc_max_gain_set(255), phy_disable_low_rate()

custom-rpcs:
  Bound to esp-hosted's peer-data channel (CONFIG_ESP_HOSTED_ENABLE_PEER_DATA_TRANSFER).
  Host calls esp_hosted_open_*; the matching handlers run on the slave.
  msg_id namespace: 0xC1750000 + ...
    SET_CHANNEL, SET_PHY_11P, SET_TX_POWER, SET_RX_GAIN, SET_AGC_MAX_GAIN,
    SET_CCA, GET_CCA_COUNTERS, RESET_CCA_COUNT, SET_LOW_RATE,
    SET_BANDWIDTH, GET_PHY_RSSI, SET_COUNTRY_PERM, GET_INFO
  Plus async event:
    OCB_FRAME (slave forwards a captured CAM/DENM payload to the host)

defaults:
  - channel:   CCH (180, 5.900 GHz)
  - tx-gated:  off (slave does not emit; host is responsible)
